{{Infobox settlement |official_name = Bakhmaro |native_name = ბახმარო |native_name_lang = ka |pushpin_map = Georgia (country) |mapsize = 280px |map_caption = Location of Bakhmaro in Georgia | image_skyline = ბახმაროს საერთო ხედი.jpg | imagesize = 250px |subdivision_type = [[Countries of the world|Country]] |subdivision_name = {{GEO}} |subdivision_type1 = [[Mkhare]] |subdivision_name1 = [[Guria]] |area_magnitude = |area_total_km2 = |area_land_km2 = |area_water_km2 = |population_as_of = 2002 |population_footnotes = |population_total = 5000 |population_metro = |population_density_km2 = |elevation_m = 1950 |timezone = Georgian Time |utc_offset = +4 |timezone_DST = <!-- No DST in Georgia since 2005 --> |utc_offset_DST = +5 |coordinates = {{coord|41|51|06|N|42|19|32|E|region:GE|display=inline,title}} |website = |footnotes = }}
'''Bakhmaro''' ({{lang-ka|ბახმარო}}) is a village in the [[Chokhatauri]] district of [[Guria]] in western [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]. It lies on the [[Bakhvistsqali river]].
==References== * [[Georgian Soviet Encyclopedia]] Vol. 2, p. 255, 1977.
