{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox building |name = Mercado dos Lavradores |native_name = |image = Mercado dos Lavradores.jpg |opening = 32°38'55.1"N 16°54'14.0"W |location = [[Funchal]], {{flagicon|Madeira}} [[Madeira]] |coordinates = {{Coord|32|38|55.1|N|16|54|14.0|W|display=it}} |building_type = |start_date = |completion_date = 25 November 1940 |cost = |roof = |top_floor = |architectural = [[Art Déco]] |observatory = |floor_count = 3 |floor_area = |elevator_count = |architect = Edmundo Tavares |structural_engineer = |main_contractor = |management = |owner = |website = http://mercados.cm-funchal.pt/ |references = }}
The '''Mercado dos Lavradores''' ("farmers' market") is a fruit, vegetable, flower and [[fish market]] in [[Funchal]], [[Madeira Island|Madeira]]. The building was designed by Edmundo Tavares and opened on 24 November 1940. The facade, main entrance and fish market contain panels of tiles depicting regional themes, executed by João Rodrigues. It is divided into a number of smaller plazas and stairways that are used as sales venues.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitfunchal.pt/en/farmers-market.html|title=Mercado dos Lavradores|publisher=Visit Funchal}}</ref>
On the night of 23 December (known locally as night of the market, Noite do Mercado in Portuguese), it is traditional for locals to meet in the market and surrounding streets singing Christmas songs, dance and drink in the nearby bars, which are open throughout the night to serve traditional drinks and especially the traditional [[Carne de vinha d'alhos]] sandwiches.<ref> {{cite web | url = http://www.visitmadeira.pt/en-gb/what-to-do/events/search/night-at-the-market | title = NIGHT AT THE MARKET | accessdate = 11 May 2017}} </ref>
