{{See also|Newfoundland outport}}

'''Outport''' is the name given in the [[United Kingdom]] for a subsidiary port built in deeper water than the original [[port]].<ref>[http://dictionary.die.net/outport Webster's Dictionary definition] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080123113047/http://dictionary.die.net/outport |date=January 23, 2008 }}</ref> The [[Port of Tilbury]] from the [[Port of London]] is a good example. [[Avonmouth]] for [[Bristol]] and, on a smaller and now historical scale,  [[Fordwich]] for [[Canterbury]] are others.

