{{Infobox settlement | name = Pantaleu | settlement_type = [[List of islands of Spain|Island]] | official_name = <!-- if different from name --> | native_name = Es Pantaleu<!-- if different from name --> | image_skyline = Es Pantaleu i Sant Elm.jpg | image_alt = | image_caption = | image_flag = | image_shield = | nickname = | motto = | image_map = | map_caption = | pushpin_map = Spain | pushpin_label_position = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Spain | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = {{flag|Spain}} | subdivision_type1 = [[Autonomous communities of Spain|Autonomous community]] | subdivision_name1 = {{flag|Balearic Islands}} | subdivision_type2 = Council | subdivision_name2 = [[Mallorca|Consell Insular de Mallorca]] | subdivision_type3 = Municipality | subdivision_name3 = [[Sant Elm]] | subdivision_type4 = | subdivision_name4 = | seat_type = <!-- [[Capital (political)|Capital]] --> | seat = | coordinates = {{coord|39|34|37|N|02|20|52|E|region:ES_type:city|display=inline}} | coordinates_footnotes = | elevation_m = | elevation_min_m = | elevation_max_m =26 | area_footnotes = | area_total_km2 = 0.024 | established_title = <!-- Founded --> | established_date = | population_footnotes = <!-- for references: use <ref> tags --> | population_total = no permanent population | population_as_of = | population_demonym = | population_note = | population_density_km2 = | blank_name_sec1 = | blank_info_sec1 = | timezone = [[Central European Time|CET]] | utc_offset = +1 | timezone_DST = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]] | utc_offset_DST = +2 | postal_code_type = | postal_code = | area_code_type = [[Telephone numbers in Spain|Dialing code]] | area_code = | leader_title = | leader_name = | leader_party = | website = | footnotes = }}
'''Es Pantaleu''' ([[Catalan language|Catalan]]) or '''El Pantaleu''' ([[Spanish language|Spanish]]) is an uninhabited [[islet]] in the [[Balearic Islands]], [[Spain]], located just off the west coast of [[Majorca]]. It is currently a [[natural park (Spain)|natural park]], part of the natural park of its neighboring island [[Dragonera]].<ref>http://www.conselldemallorca.net/dragonera/dades.php?lang=EN</ref> It has an area of 2,4 ha and its highest point is 26 m [[Sea level#AMSL|AMSL]].
==Geography== Geologically speaking, Pantaleu is an emerged part of the [[Baetic System|geologic system running southwest-northeast]] in the [[Iberian Peninsula]]. This runs from the [[Province of Málaga]] through [[Cap de la Nau]] and then gets submerged under the [[Mediterranean Sea]]. It surfaces again to form the island of [[Ibiza]], the [[Serra de Tramuntana|Tramuntana Range]] in the island of Majorca and Pantaleu itself.
The island is a part of the municipality of [[Andratx]], which is, along with [[Sant Elm]] (both in nearby Majorca), the closest towns to the island.
==History== This islet gained historical importance in 1229 when [[James I of Aragon]] in September of this year dropped anchor by this island in order to protect his ships from the storm. They explored the coast of Majorca from here and chose the strand near today's [[Santa Ponsa|Santa Ponça]] as an ideal landing point for the Crusaders to start the [[Reconquista]] of the [[Balearic Islands]]. The gulf of Sant Elm proved to be a good place for defense.
Lying about 300&nbsp;m from the strand of Sant Elm, the island is a popular destination for good swimmers. Since 1998 it belongs to the Dragonera nature reserve and must not be entered.
